    <stitle>HENDRICKSON SUSPENSION SYSTEMS - BUSHING REPLACEMENT - TORQUE RODS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="5">
        <title>TORQUE RODS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If you are using special tools, follow their instructions. If you are using standard and
                        shop-made tools, use the following instructions.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Torque rods have three different style attaching ends:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Straddle-mount--two-bolt (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300618">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <figure id="f0300618" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300618" filename="../figg03/G0300618.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Torque Rod Attaching Ends</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>A.CROSSMEMBER MOUNT</callout1>
                    <callout1>B.BACK TO BACK MOUNT</callout1>
                    <callout1>1.REINFORCING PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.TORQUE ROD FRAME BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.TORQUE ROD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Through-bolt--single-bolt (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300619">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <figure id="f0300619" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300619" filename="../figg03/G0300619.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Axle Housing/Inner Sleeve of Torque Rod</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.AXLE HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.THROUGH-BOLT SLEEVE CARTRIDGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.TORQUE ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.OFFSET PIN CARTRIDGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.TORQUE ROD MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>7.HEX HEAD BOLT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Tapered stud (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300620">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <figure id="f0300620" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300620" filename="../figg03/G0300620.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Removing Tapered Stud Ends</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.TORQUE ROD AXLE BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.TORQUE ROD FRAME BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.NYLON INSERT LOCK NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.STRIKE HERE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Straddle-Mount Torque Rods</title>
            <para>Straddle-mount torque rods can be mounted either on the crossmember, or back-to-back.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove straddle-mount torque rod ends, remove the locknut, bolts, washers and any
                    adjustment shims (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300618">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press out the worn end. Install a cartridge replacement.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the torque rod at the bracket, then assemble the bolts, washers, locknuts and
                    any adjustment shims as noted. Tighten to the values found in the the
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Through-Bolt Torque Rods</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove through-bolt torque rods, first remove the hex head bolt from the axle
                    housing/inner sleeve of the torque rod end (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300619">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press out the worn end and install a cartridge replacement.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the straddle-mount ends as needed (with offset pin cartridges) at the torque rod
                    mounting end brackets, per the above instructions for straddle-mount torque rods.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the axle housing end of the torque rod, using the hex bolt removed in step 1.
                    Tighten to the value found in the the
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Tapered Stud Torque Rods</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove tapered stud ends, loosen the locknut and rap the axle bracket with a hammer
                    to break the stud free (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300620">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press out the worn end. Install a cartridge replacement.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the bracket hole of any foreign matter. Place the stud in the bracket and assemble
                    the locknut with spacer washer (if so equipped). Tighten the locknut to the value found in the
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rap the axle bracket with a hammer (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300620">Figure 20</hotlnk>), then tighten the locknut again to the value found in
                    the
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Transverse Torque Rods</title>
            <para>
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300621">Figure 21</hotlnk>and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300622">Figure 22</hotlnk>show the application of transverse torque rods.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0300621" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300621" filename="../figg03/G0300621.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Transverse Torque Rods - Application</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.TRANSVERSE TORQUE RODS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0300622" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300622" filename="../figg03/G0300622.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Transverse Torque Rods - View</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.TORQUE ROD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.FORWARD REAR AXLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.REAR REAR AXLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.AXLE SPACING</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.TORQUE ROD FRAME BRACKET (2 REQUIRED)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.ALL LOCKNUTS GRADE "C"</callout1>
                    <callout1>7.TORQUE ROD AXLE BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>8.ALL BOLTS GRADE 8, HARDENED WASHER (BOTH SIDES)</callout1>
                    <callout1>9.FRAME BACK-UP PLATE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
